---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Products"
  description="The Poesis stack: SIE (the GSM engine and reference implementation) and ITIP (the first domain application), plus the platform components."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">The stack</p>
      <h1>The canonical GSM implementation.</h1>
      <p class="lead">Poesis is the software editor of the reference stack: the engine that hosts GSM, the first domain application built on it, and the platform components around them.</p>
      <div class="hero-cta">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact">Request a demo</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="https://github.com/poesis-cloud">Browse the repos</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="card"><span class="tag">SIE</span><h3>Systemic Intelligence Engine</h3><p>The GSM engine and reference implementation — Definition Manager, Operator, Blackboard, and supporting services. Hosts GSM; enforces the lifecycle and conformance.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><span class="tag">ITIP</span><h3>IT Intelligence Platform</h3><p>The first domain application built on SIE — translating GSM into IT intelligence and governance for real organizations.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><span class="tag tag--muted">Platform</span><h3>Components</h3><p>Definition database, event bus, schema registry, OpenTelemetry collector — the substrate the stack runs on.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><span class="tag tag--muted">Open core</span><h3>How you run it</h3><p>A free community edition, a paid enterprise edition, a managed SaaS, or on-prem integration and administration in regulated and sovereign environments.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Editor · SaaS · On-prem</p>
      <h2>Adopt it the way your environment demands.</h2>
      <p class="lead">Start free, scale to enterprise, run it as a managed service, or deploy and administer it inside your own perimeter. Same stack, three commercial paths.</p>
      <p><a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/services">Talk to us about deployment →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
